    <field name="description">
      <value>As an example, if in a xml doc file you have some HTML like this:

&lt;p&gt;
you should create a &amp;lt;monorail&amp;gt; element in your web.config &amp;amp; something else
&lt;/p&gt;

The HTML entities are changed to &lt;, &gt; and &amp; respectively in the outputted HTML.

However, when you have XML comments in the code sections like this:

/// &lt;summary&gt;

It is outputted like this:

&lt;span class="rem"&gt;/// &amp;lt;summary&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;

So the code sections are HTML encoded while the rest of the text is HTML decoded.</value>
